example_quotes: Medical Student: "Any changes in your bowel movements at all?"
Patient: "No."
Medical Student: "Besides that, have you been having any symptoms of fevers, chills, sore throat?"
Patient: "no."
Medical Student: "...are you bringing up any sputum?"
Patient: "Yeah, that yeah I do."
Medical Student: "Do you get any other symptoms besides the, uh, sneezing and runny nose?"
Patient: "...I also wake up in the morning with this like sore throat and have just cough and clear out my, you know clear my throat."
Patient: "I must have been like 8 years old or 9 years old that I remember, but I think I've had it before that as well as my mom tells me."
Medical Student: "Do you have that at all now?"
Patient: "No, no, I don't."
Medical Student: "Any kind of fatigue or tiredness throughout the day?"
Patient: "I do feel more fatigued when I have these symptoms."
Medical Student: "Besides that, have you been having any symptoms of fevers, chills, sore throat?"
Patient: "no."
Medical Student: "Any headaches?"
Patient: "No."
Medical Student: "Any nausea or vomiting?"
Patient: "no."
Medical Student: "Do you have a sensation of like anything kind of dripping down your throat like after you wake up like just a build up?"
Patient: "Yeah yeah I do."
Patient: "Hi, I've I've just been. I've been sneezing a lot and I have this runny nose."
Medical Student: "Sorry just one more question, any loss of sense of taste or smell?"
Patient: "Yeah, it's hard to smell and my nose is stuffy, but no loss of taste."
Patient: "Hi, I've I've just been. I've been sneezing a lot and I have this runny nose."
Patient: "...I also wake up in the morning with this like sore throat and have just cough and clear out my, you know clear my throat."
Medical Student: "Any changes to your appetite or weight?"
Patient: "I've been losing weight, but I've been dieting and working out more."
Medical Student: "How much weight would you say you've lost over the last few months?"
Patient: "I've lost about four pounds in the past four, five months."
Medical Student: "Any trouble urinating?"
Patient: "no."
Medical Student: "Any nausea or vomiting?"
Patient: "no."
